23// This analysis infers types for all operations. It does so by running a
24// fixpoint analysis on the input graph in order to properly type PhiOps. The
25// analysis visits blocks in order and computes operation types using
26// Turboshaft's Typer. For Goto operations, the analysis checks if this is a
27// back edge (the Goto's target is a loop block with an index less than the
28// index of the current block). If this is the case, the analysis revisits the
29// loop block (this is when ProcessBlock<true> is called). During this revisit,
30// two things are different to the normal processing of a block:
31//
32// 1.) PhiOps are handled specially, which means applying proper
33// widening/narrowing mechanics to accelerate termination while still computing
34// somewhat precise types for Phis. 2.) If the type of any of the loop's Phis
35// grows, we reset the index of unprocessed blocks to the block after the loop
36// header, such that the entire loop body is revisited with the new type
37// information.
38class TypeInferenceAnalysis {
39 public:
40 explicit TypeInferenceAnalysis(const Graph& graph, Zone* phase_zone)
41 : graph_(graph),
42 // TODO(nicohartmann@): Might put types back into phase_zone once we
43 // don't store them in the graph anymore.
44 types_(graph.op_id_count(), Type{}, graph.graph_zone(), &graph),
45 table_(phase_zone),
46 op_to_key_mapping_(phase_zone, &graph),
47 block_to_snapshot_mapping_(graph.block_count(), base::nullopt,
48 phase_zone),
49 predecessors_(phase_zone),
50 graph_zone_(graph.graph_zone()) {}
51
52 GrowingOpIndexSidetable<Type> Run(
53 GrowingBlockSidetable<std::vector<std::pair<OpIndex, Type>>>*
54 block_refinements = nullptr) {
55#ifdef DEBUG
56 block_refinements_ = block_refinements;
57#endif // DEBUG
58 TURBOSHAFT_TRACE_TYPING("=== Running Type Inference Analysis ===\n");
59 for (uint32_t unprocessed_index = 0;
60 unprocessed_index < graph_.block_count();) {
61 BlockIndex block_index = static_cast<BlockIndex>(unprocessed_index);
62 ++unprocessed_index;
63 const Block& block = graph_.Get(block_index);
64
65#ifdef DEBUG
66 if (V8_UNLIKELY(v8_flags.turboshaft_trace_typing)) {
67 std::stringstream os;
68 os << block.kind() << " " << block.index().id();
69 TURBOSHAFT_TRACE_TYPING("=== %s ===\n", os.str().c_str());
70 }
71#endif // DEBUG
72
73 ProcessBlock<false>(block, &unprocessed_index);
74 }
75 TURBOSHAFT_TRACE_TYPING("=== Completed Type Inference Analysis ===\n");
76
77 return std::move(types_);
78 }
79
80 template <bool revisit_loop_header>
81 void ProcessBlock(const Block& block, uint32_t* unprocessed_index) {
82 DCHECK_IMPLIES(revisit_loop_header, block.IsLoop());
83
84 // Seal the current block first.
85 if (table_.IsSealed()) {
86 DCHECK_NULL(current_block_);
87 } else {
88 // If we process a new block while the previous one is still unsealed, we
89 // finalize it.
90 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(current_block_);
91 DCHECK(current_block_->index().valid());
92 block_to_snapshot_mapping_[current_block_->index()] = table_.Seal();
93 current_block_ = nullptr;
94 }
95
96 // Collect the snapshots of all predecessors.
97 {
98 predecessors_.clear();
99 for (const Block* pred : block.PredecessorsIterable()) {
100 base::Optional<table_t::Snapshot> pred_snapshot =
101 block_to_snapshot_mapping_[pred->index()];
102 if (pred_snapshot.has_value()) {
103 predecessors_.push_back(pred_snapshot.value());
104 } else {
105 // The only case where we might not have a snapshot for the
106 // predecessor is when we visit a loop header for the first time.
107 DCHECK(block.IsLoop() && pred == block.LastPredecessor() &&
108 !revisit_loop_header);
109 }
110 }
111 std::reverse(predecessors_.begin(), predecessors_.end());
112 }
113
114 // Start a new snapshot for this block by merging information from
115 // predecessors.
116 {
117 auto MergeTypes = [&](table_t::Key,
118 base::Vector<const Type> predecessors) -> Type {
119 DCHECK_GT(predecessors.size(), 0);
120 Type result_type = predecessors[0];
121 for (size_t i = 1; i < predecessors.size(); ++i) {
122 result_type =
123 Type::LeastUpperBound(result_type, predecessors[i], graph_zone_);
124 }
125 return result_type;
126 };
127
128 table_.StartNewSnapshot(base::VectorOf(predecessors_), MergeTypes);
129 }
130
131 // Check if the predecessor is a branch that allows us to refine a few
132 // types.
133 DCHECK_IMPLIES(revisit_loop_header, block.PredecessorCount() == 2);
134 if (block.PredecessorCount() == 1) {
135 Block* predecessor = block.LastPredecessor();
136 const Operation& terminator = predecessor->LastOperation(graph_);
137 if (const BranchOp* branch = terminator.TryCast<BranchOp>()) {
138 DCHECK(branch->if_true == &block || branch->if_false == &block);
139 RefineTypesAfterBranch(branch, &block, branch->if_true == &block);
140 }
141 }
142 current_block_ = &block;
143
144 bool loop_needs_revisit = false;
145 auto op_range = graph_.OperationIndices(block);
146 for (auto it = op_range.begin(); it != op_range.end(); ++it) {
147 OpIndex index = *it;
148 const Operation& op = graph_.Get(index);
149
150 switch (op.opcode) {
151 case Opcode::kBranch:
152 case Opcode::kDeoptimize:
153 case Opcode::kDeoptimizeIf:
154 case Opcode::kFrameState:
155 case Opcode::kReturn:
156 case Opcode::kStore:
157 case Opcode::kRetain:
158 case Opcode::kUnreachable:
159 case Opcode::kSwitch:
160 case Opcode::kTuple:
161 case Opcode::kStaticAssert:
162 case Opcode::kDebugBreak:
163 case Opcode::kDebugPrint:
164#if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
165 case Opcode::kGlobalSet:
166 case Opcode::kTrapIf:
167#endif
168 case Opcode::kCheckException:
169 // These operations do not produce any output that needs to be typed.
170 DCHECK_EQ(0, op.outputs_rep().size());
171 break;
172 case Opcode::kCheckTurboshaftTypeOf:
173 ProcessCheckTurboshaftTypeOf(index,
174 op.Cast<CheckTurboshaftTypeOfOp>());
175 break;
176 case Opcode::kComparison:
177 ProcessComparison(index, op.Cast<ComparisonOp>());
178 break;
179 case Opcode::kConstant:
180 ProcessConstant(index, op.Cast<ConstantOp>());
181 break;
182 case Opcode::kFloatBinop:
183 ProcessFloatBinop(index, op.Cast<FloatBinopOp>());
184 break;
185 case Opcode::kOverflowCheckedBinop:
186 ProcessOverflowCheckedBinop(index, op.Cast<OverflowCheckedBinopOp>());
187 break;
188 case Opcode::kProjection:
189 ProcessProjection(index, op.Cast<ProjectionOp>());
190 break;
191 case Opcode::kWordBinop:
192 ProcessWordBinop(V<Word>::Cast(index), op.Cast<WordBinopOp>());
193 break;
194 case Opcode::kWord32PairBinop:
195 case Opcode::kAtomicWord32Pair:
196 case Opcode::kPendingLoopPhi:
197 // Input graph must not contain these op codes.
198 UNREACHABLE();
199 case Opcode::kPhi:
200 if constexpr (revisit_loop_header) {
201 loop_needs_revisit =
202 ProcessLoopPhi(index, op.Cast<PhiOp>()) || loop_needs_revisit;
203 } else {
204 ProcessPhi(index, op.Cast<PhiOp>());
205 }
206 break;
207 case Opcode::kGoto: {
208 const GotoOp& gto = op.Cast<GotoOp>();
209 // Check if this is a backedge.
210 if (gto.destination->IsLoop()) {
211 if (gto.destination->index() < current_block_->index()) {
212 ProcessBlock<true>(*gto.destination, unprocessed_index);
213 } else if (gto.destination->index() == current_block_->index()) {
214 // This is a single block loop. We must only revisit the current
215 // header block if we actually need to, in order to prevent
216 // infinite recursion.
217 if (!revisit_loop_header || loop_needs_revisit) {
218 ProcessBlock<true>(*gto.destination, unprocessed_index);
219 }
220 }
221 }
222 break;
223 }
224
225 default:
226 // TODO(nicohartmann@): Support remaining operations. For now we
227 // compute fallback types.
228 if (op.outputs_rep().size() > 0) {
229 constexpr bool allow_narrowing = false;
230 constexpr bool is_fallback_for_unsupported_operation = true;
231 SetType(index,
232 Typer::TypeForRepresentation(op.outputs_rep(), graph_zone_),
233 allow_narrowing, is_fallback_for_unsupported_operation);
234 }
235 break;
236 case Opcode::kLoadRootRegister:
237 SetType(index,
238 Typer::TypeForRepresentation(op.outputs_rep(), graph_zone_));
239 break;
240 }
241 }
242
243 if constexpr (revisit_loop_header) {
244 if (loop_needs_revisit) {
245 // This is a loop header and the loop body needs to be revisited. Reset
246 // {unprocessed_index} to the loop header's successor.
247 *unprocessed_index =
248 std::min(*unprocessed_index, block.index().id() + 1);
249 }
250 }
251 }
252
253 void ProcessCheckTurboshaftTypeOf(OpIndex index,
254 const CheckTurboshaftTypeOfOp& check) {
255 Type input_type = GetType(check.input());
256
257 if (input_type.IsSubtypeOf(check.type)) {
258 TURBOSHAFT_TRACE_TYPING_OK(
259 "CTOF %3d:%-40s\n P: %3d:%-40s ~~> %s\n", index.id(),
260 graph_.Get(index).ToString().substr(0, 40).c_str(),
261 check.input().id(),
262 graph_.Get(check.input()).ToString().substr(0, 40).c_str(),
263 input_type.ToString().c_str());
264 } else if (check.successful) {
265 FATAL(
266 "Checking type %s of operation %d:%s failed after it passed in a "
267 "previous phase",
268 check.type.ToString().c_str(), check.input().id(),
269 graph_.Get(check.input()).ToString().c_str());
270 } else {
271 TURBOSHAFT_TRACE_TYPING_FAIL(
272 "CTOF %3d:%-40s\n F: %3d:%-40s ~~> %s\n", index.id(),
273 graph_.Get(index).ToString().substr(0, 40).c_str(),
274 check.input().id(),
275 graph_.Get(check.input()).ToString().substr(0, 40).c_str(),
276 input_type.ToString().c_str());
277 }
278 }
279
280 void ProcessComparison(OpIndex index, const ComparisonOp& comparison) {
281 Type left_type = GetType(comparison.left());
282 Type right_type = GetType(comparison.right());
283
284 Type result_type = Typer::TypeComparison(
285 left_type, right_type, comparison.rep, comparison.kind, graph_zone_);
286 SetType(index, result_type);
287 }
288
289 void ProcessConstant(OpIndex index, const ConstantOp& constant) {
290 Type type = Typer::TypeConstant(constant.kind, constant.storage);
291 SetType(index, type);
292 }
293
294 void ProcessFloatBinop(OpIndex index, const FloatBinopOp& binop) {
295 Type left_type = GetType(binop.left());
296 Type right_type = GetType(binop.right());
297
298 Type result_type = Typer::TypeFloatBinop(left_type, right_type, binop.kind,
299 binop.rep, graph_zone_);
300 SetType(index, result_type);
301 }
302
303 bool ProcessLoopPhi(OpIndex index, const PhiOp& phi) {
304 Type old_type = GetTypeAtDefinition(index);
305 Type new_type = ComputeTypeForPhi(phi);
306
307 if (old_type.IsInvalid()) {
308 SetType(index, new_type);
309 return true;
310 }
311
312 // If the new type is smaller, we narrow it without revisiting the loop.
313 if (new_type.IsSubtypeOf(old_type)) {
314 TURBOSHAFT_TRACE_TYPING_OK(
315 "LOOP %3d:%-40s (FIXPOINT)\n N: %-40s ~~> %-40s\n", index.id(),
316 graph_.Get(index).ToString().substr(0, 40).c_str(),
317 old_type.ToString().c_str(), new_type.ToString().c_str());
318
319 constexpr bool allow_narrowing = true;
320 SetType(index, new_type, allow_narrowing);
321 return false;
322 }
323
324 // Otherwise, the new type is larger and we widen and revisit the loop.
325 TURBOSHAFT_TRACE_TYPING_OK(
326 "LOOP %3d:%-40s (REVISIT)\n W: %-40s ~~> %-40s\n", index.id(),
327 graph_.Get(index).ToString().substr(0, 40).c_str(),
328 old_type.ToString().c_str(), new_type.ToString().c_str());
329
330 if (!old_type.IsNone()) {
331 new_type = Widen(old_type, new_type);
332 }
333 SetType(index, new_type);
334 return true;
335 }
336
337 void ProcessOverflowCheckedBinop(OpIndex index,
338 const OverflowCheckedBinopOp& binop) {
339 Type left_type = GetType(binop.left());
340 Type right_type = GetType(binop.right());
341
342 Type result_type = Typer::TypeOverflowCheckedBinop(
343 left_type, right_type, binop.kind, binop.rep, graph_zone_);
344 SetType(index, result_type);
345 }
346
347 void ProcessPhi(OpIndex index, const PhiOp& phi) {
348 Type result_type = ComputeTypeForPhi(phi);
349 SetType(index, result_type);
350 }
351
352 void ProcessProjection(OpIndex index, const ProjectionOp& projection) {
353 Type input_type = GetType(projection.input());
354
355 Type result_type;
356 if (input_type.IsNone()) {
357 result_type = Type::None();
358 } else if (input_type.IsTuple()) {
359 const TupleType& tuple = input_type.AsTuple();
360 DCHECK_LT(projection.index, tuple.size());
361 result_type = tuple.element(projection.index);
362 DCHECK(result_type.IsSubtypeOf(
363 Typer::TypeForRepresentation(projection.rep)));
364 } else {
365 result_type = Typer::TypeForRepresentation(projection.rep);
366 }
367
368 SetType(index, result_type);
369 }
370
371 void ProcessWordBinop(V<Word> index, const WordBinopOp& binop) {
372 Type left_type = GetType(binop.left());
373 Type right_type = GetType(binop.right());
374
375 Type result_type = Typer::TypeWordBinop(left_type, right_type, binop.kind,
376 binop.rep, graph_zone_);
377 SetType(index, result_type);
378 }
379
380 Type ComputeTypeForPhi(const PhiOp& phi) {
381 // Word64 values are truncated to word32 implicitly, we need to handle this
382 // here.
383 auto MaybeTruncate = [&](Type t) -> Type {
384 if (t.IsNone()) return t;
385 if (phi.rep == RegisterRepresentation::Word32()) {
386 return Typer::TruncateWord32Input(t, true, graph_zone_);
387 }
388 return t;
389 };
390
391 Type result_type =
392 MaybeTruncate(GetTypeOrDefault(phi.inputs()[0], Type::None()));
393 for (size_t i = 1; i < phi.inputs().size(); ++i) {
394 Type input_type =
395 MaybeTruncate(GetTypeOrDefault(phi.inputs()[i], Type::None()));
396 result_type = Type::LeastUpperBound(result_type, input_type, graph_zone_);
397 }
398 return result_type;
399 }
400
401 void RefineTypesAfterBranch(const BranchOp* branch, const Block* new_block,
402 bool then_branch) {
403 TURBOSHAFT_TRACE_TYPING_OK("Br %3d:%-40s\n", graph_.Index(*branch).id(),
404 branch->ToString().substr(0, 40).c_str());
405
406 Typer::BranchRefinements refinements(
407 [this](OpIndex index) { return GetType(index); },
408 [&](OpIndex index, const Type& refined_type) {
409 RefineOperationType(new_block, index, refined_type,
410 then_branch ? 'T' : 'F');
411 });
412
413 // Inspect branch condition.
414 const Operation& condition = graph_.Get(branch->condition());
415 refinements.RefineTypes(condition, then_branch, graph_zone_);
416 }
417
418 void RefineOperationType(const Block* new_block, OpIndex op, const Type& type,
419 char case_for_tracing) {
420 DCHECK(op.valid());
421 DCHECK(!type.IsInvalid());
422
423 TURBOSHAFT_TRACE_TYPING_OK(" %c: %3d:%-40s ~~> %s\n", case_for_tracing,
424 op.id(),
425 graph_.Get(op).ToString().substr(0, 40).c_str(),
426 type.ToString().c_str());
427
428 auto key_opt = op_to_key_mapping_[op];
429 DCHECK(key_opt.has_value());
430 table_.Set(*key_opt, type);
431
432#ifdef DEBUG
433 if (block_refinements_) {
434 (*block_refinements_)[new_block->index()].emplace_back(op, type);
435 }
436#endif
437
438 // TODO(nicohartmann@): One could push the refined type deeper into the
439 // operations.
440 }
441
442 void SetType(OpIndex index, Type result_type, bool allow_narrowing = false,
443 bool is_fallback_for_unsupported_operation = false) {
444 DCHECK(!result_type.IsInvalid());
445
446 if (auto key_opt = op_to_key_mapping_[index]) {
447 table_.Set(*key_opt, result_type);
448 types_[index] = result_type;
449 } else {
450 auto key = table_.NewKey(Type::None());
451 op_to_key_mapping_[index] = key;
452 table_.Set(key, result_type);
453 types_[index] = result_type;
454 }
455
456 if (!is_fallback_for_unsupported_operation) {
457 TURBOSHAFT_TRACE_TYPING_OK(
458 "Type %3d:%-40s ==> %s\n", index.id(),
459 graph_.Get(index).ToString().substr(0, 40).c_str(),
460 result_type.ToString().c_str());
461 } else {
462 // TODO(nicohartmann@): Remove the fallback case once all operations are
463 // supported.
464 TURBOSHAFT_TRACE_TYPING_FAIL(
465 "TODO %3d:%-40s ==> %s\n", index.id(),
466 graph_.Get(index).ToString().substr(0, 40).c_str(),
467 result_type.ToString().c_str());
468 }
469 }
470
471 Type GetTypeOrInvalid(const OpIndex index) {
472 if (auto key = op_to_key_mapping_[index]) return table_.Get(*key);
473 return Type::Invalid();
474 }
475
476 Type GetTypeOrDefault(OpIndex index, const Type& default_type) {
477 Type t = GetTypeOrInvalid(index);
478 if (t.IsInvalid()) return default_type;
479 return t;
480 }
481
482 Type GetType(OpIndex index) {
483 Type t = GetTypeOrInvalid(index);
484 if (t.IsInvalid()) {
485 // TODO(nicohartmann@): This is a fallback mechanism as long as not all
486 // operations are properly typed. Remove this once typing is complete.
487 const Operation& op = graph_.Get(index);
488 return Typer::TypeForRepresentation(op.outputs_rep(), graph_zone_);
489 }
490 return t;
491 }
492
493 Type GetTypeAtDefinition(OpIndex index) const { return types_[index]; }
494
495 Type Widen(const Type& old_type, const Type& new_type) {
496 if (new_type.IsAny()) return new_type;
497 // We might have to relax this eventually and widen different types.
498 DCHECK_EQ(old_type.kind(), new_type.kind());
499
500 switch (old_type.kind()) {
501 case Type::Kind::kWord32:
502 // TODO(nicohartmann@): Reevaluate whether exponential widening is
503 // better here.
504 //
505 // return WordOperationTyper<32>::WidenExponential(old_type.AsWord32(),
506 // new_type.AsWord32(), graph_zone_);
507 return WordOperationTyper<32>::WidenMaximal(
508 old_type.AsWord32(), new_type.AsWord32(), graph_zone_);
509 case Type::Kind::kWord64:
510 // TODO(nicohartmann@): Reevaluate whether exponential widening is
511 // better here.
512 //
513 // return WordOperationTyper<64>::WidenExponential(old_type.AsWord64(),
514 // new_type.AsWord64(), graph_zone_);
515 return WordOperationTyper<64>::WidenMaximal(
516 old_type.AsWord64(), new_type.AsWord64(), graph_zone_);
517 case Type::Kind::kFloat32:
518 // TODO(nicohartmann@): Implement proper widening.
519 return Float32Type::Any();
520 case Type::Kind::kFloat64:
521 // TODO(nicohartmann@): Implement proper widening.
522 return Float64Type::Any();
523 default:
524 // TODO(nicohartmann@): Handle remaining cases.
525 UNREACHABLE();
526 }
527 }
528
529 private:
530 const Graph& graph_;
531 GrowingOpIndexSidetable<Type> types_;
532 using table_t = SnapshotTable<Type>;
533 table_t table_;
534 const Block* current_block_ = nullptr;
535 GrowingOpIndexSidetable<base::Optional<table_t::Key>> op_to_key_mapping_;
536 GrowingBlockSidetable<base::Optional<table_t::Snapshot>>
537 block_to_snapshot_mapping_;
538 // {predecessors_} is used during merging, but we use an instance variable for
539 // it, in order to save memory and not reallocate it for each merge.
540 ZoneVector<table_t::Snapshot> predecessors_;
541 Zone* graph_zone_;
542
543#ifdef DEBUG
544 // {block_refinements_} are only stored for tracing in Debug builds.
545 GrowingBlockSidetable<std::vector<std::pair<OpIndex, Type>>>*
546 block_refinements_ = nullptr;
547#endif
548};
